# {{name}}

A [Twill DB](https://github.com/bihaviour/twill-db) starter for **Node** — a
serverless OLTP database embedded in-process via `@twilldb/node` (koffi FFI). No
server to run, no infrastructure to provision.

## Run it

```bash
npm install
npm start
```

Requires **Node ≥ 22.18** (to run `.ts` directly via type stripping). The native
engine ships with `@twilldb/node` as a per-platform optional dependency, so there
is no `cargo build` step. To point at a libengine you built yourself, set
`TWILLDB_ENGINE_PATH=/abs/path/libengine.{so,dylib,dll}`.

## Frameworks

The same `app.ts` logic drops into any Node-based framework — Next.js, Astro,
Nuxt, Remix, SvelteKit, Vite SSR. Open **one** `Database` per server process and
reuse it across requests (the engine is a single writer per database). On the
Edge runtime, FFI is unavailable — keep the database on the Node.js runtime (in
Next.js, add `export const runtime = "nodejs"` to the route).

This same code also runs on **Bun**: change the import to `@twilldb/bun`.

## Storage backend

The backend is chosen entirely by the connection string in `app.ts`:

| Scheme | Backend |
| --- | --- |
| `file://…` | embedded, persists to a local file (this starter's default) |
| `s3://` · `r2://` · `gs://` | storage-disaggregated; credentials come from the environment |

This project is configured for `{{db_url}}`.
